^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, first the bidding. Everything up through 3C is fine. Some might even bid 4C with my hand. But, Patti should not pass. I assume Patti you realized 3C was weak. Technically I guess that is an alert. There is a convention known as a "responsive double" that is perfect for her hand. Some people play, that as responder to an overcaller, if there are two unbid suits remaining, and you double, that is sort of like a negative double, it shows those 2 suits.|
PG| ***** 80 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, the auction 1x-1y-2x (or 3x)-double is a "responsive double" showing the 2 unbid suits as is the auction 1x-double-1y-double. The first auction is more useful. In this hand, it turns out Patti has the perfect responsive double, showing hearts and spades. It does turn out, with the diamond finesse working, you do make 4S, but it will be rare that Dee has a 4 card major.|
PG| ***** 81 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|However, in general I am not a big fan of responsive doubles. I would simply bid 3D with Patti's hand.|
