NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|1C-P-2N shows 11-12 and is invitational whether or not there is an intervening bid. You have to remember, as responder, if you have a game forcing hand, it is  your responsibility to make sure you get to game. Therefore, you must make either a forcing bid or bid game. An opener opposite an opener should make game. If partner opens, and you have an opener, you should force to game. Let me explain further. Had Patti passed then 1C-P-2N and 1C-P-3N deny a 4-card major, and should be avoided if at all possible, as they take up a lot of bidding room. |
PG| ***** 93 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|On the other hand, when there is an overcall such as to the particular auction 1C-1S-?, 
1N is 8-10 (you need not bid with 6 or 7) 
2N is 11-12, and 
3N is 13+. They all tend to promise a spade stopper (although you can be a bit more lax with 1N). One spade stopper will do, even with 2N and 3N, although at the higher levels it is better if, when you have one stopper, you have some length in the suit. Next, is your undo so you can select the correct bid in this auction.|
